====Derived terms====
*[[പള്ളീലച്ഛ&#3439;]]..........Christian priest.
*[[വല്ല്യച്ഛ&#3439;]]..........Older paternal uncle. Literally "big father".
*[[കൊച്ചച്ഛ&#3439;]]..........Younger paternal uncle. Literally "small father".
====Synonyms====

*[[പിതാവു&#3405;]]..........This word was derived from Sanskrit ''pitr'' and is considered very formal.
*[[തന്ത]]..........This is a very colloquial and rude term meaning father.
*[[ബാപ്പ]]..........This is the word that most Muslims who speak malayalam use for father.
*[[അപ്പ&#3439;]]''or'' [[അപ്പച്ച&#3439;]].......... These are usually used by Christians who use അച്ഛ&#3439; to refer to priests (with irregular vocative അച്ഛോ [atʃtʃhoː] most of the time).

